<HEADLINE> Mbeki Sworn in as South African President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PRETORIA, June 16 (Xinhua) - South African outgoing president
Nelson Mandela formally handed power to Thabo Mbeki at the
government headquarters here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki, 56, was sworn in as the second all-race-elected
president by Constitutional Court President Arthur Chaskalson.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki said, "I swear that I will be faithful to the republic
of South Africa and will obey, observe, uphold and maintain the
constitution and all other law of the republic." 
</P>
